Author: Elodie Courtois
reference: Courtois E. 2010. Le parfum de la defense des plantes en foret amazonienne. Ph.D. thesis; Universite de Toulouse; Toulouse; France. https://www.theses.fr/2010TOU30266.
Notes: Assumed SLA was actually in m2/kg (based on magnitude). Assumed saplings to be in the shade and trees to be fully illuminated (assumption because they used climbers). Conversion from leaf toughness (N) to leaf force to puncture (kN/m) assumed cross-section diameter of 4.75mm based on instrument used (Chatillon E-DFE-2) and communication with Chatillon. Number of samples is the number of individuals sampled for each species; size class and site.

Notes: Assumed SLA was actually in m2/kg (based on magnitude). Assumed saplings to be in the shade and trees to be fully illuminated (assumption because they used climbers). Conversion from leaf toughness (N) to leaf force to puncture (kN/m) assumed cross-section diameter of 4.75mm based on instrument used (Chatillon E-DFE-2) and communication with Chatillon. Number of samples is the number of individuals sampled for each species; size class and site.
